{% block content %}
  <p class="crumb"><a href="/communities">Communities</a> › <a href="/communities/sagamok">Sagamok Anishnawbek</a> › One Seat, or One Salary</p>

  <p class="eyebrow">Sagamok Anishnawbek · A member's ask</p>
  <h1>One Seat, or One Salary</h1>
  <p class="lead">Seven of Sagamok's twelve elected Councillors also hold a paid staff or executive position with the Nation or a company it owns. Every fact on this page comes from Sagamok's own public website and public filings. It is presented so members can see it in one place, and it comes with a simple ask.</p>

  {% set banner_body %}<strong>Member-compiled and unofficial.</strong> This is a member-compiled summary, not an official communication of Sagamok Anishnawbek. <a href="/about#corrections">Tell us what we got wrong</a> and we will correct it.{% endset %}
  {% include 'components/notice.html.twig' with { variant: 'caveat', body: banner_body, label: 'About this page' } only %}

  {% include 'components/section_heading.html.twig' with { title: 'What the public record shows' } only %}
  <p>According to Sagamok's own public staff directory, the Chief and Council page, and the Z'gamok Enterprises website, these Council members also hold a paid role:</p>

